00:31:41,200 --> 00:31:43,943
[SPEAKER_18]: I mean, honestly, I'm happy to have a conversation with you.

379
00:31:43,963 --> 00:31:44,043
[SPEAKER_18]: Okay.

380
00:31:45,501 --> 00:31:47,282
[SPEAKER_18]: I want to review a little bit more closely.

381
00:31:47,342 --> 00:31:50,424
[SPEAKER_18]: I know that we did this work several years ago.

382
00:31:51,084 --> 00:31:55,066
[SPEAKER_18]: So the handbook should reflect the work that was done several years ago.

383
00:31:55,746 --> 00:32:00,609
[SPEAKER_18]: There is also, at the elementary level, we are responsive classroom.

384
00:32:01,169 --> 00:32:07,772
[SPEAKER_18]: And part of the responsive classroom approach is that consequences for student behavior are logical.

385
00:32:08,453 --> 00:32:14,396
[SPEAKER_18]: And so we've talked a great deal about the loss of recess

386
00:32:15,589 --> 00:32:28,377
[SPEAKER_18]: when it's logical is for clearly when children have unsafe bodies on the playground or during recess, a time to just step away, calm down, get regulated again.

387
00:32:28,717 --> 00:32:29,717
[SPEAKER_18]: That's logical.

388
00:32:29,837 --> 00:32:31,018
[SPEAKER_18]: That's a logical consequence.

389
00:32:34,509 --> 00:32:47,259
[SPEAKER_18]: If there are situations, there should not be language in there, but if there are situations where we're, you know, taking recess away for not bringing in homework, that's not part of the, or, or, and aligned to the spirit of the school committee policy.

390
00:32:47,359 --> 00:32:50,362
[SPEAKER_18]: So, I'm happy to have a conversation with you and review that with.

391
00:32:51,632 --> 00:32:51,993
[SPEAKER_10]: Thank you.

392
00:32:52,033 --> 00:33:01,598
[SPEAKER_10]: I think just being more explicit, like any student who is referred to the main office could have recess taken away.

393
00:33:01,618 --> 00:33:11,664
[SPEAKER_10]: I mean, I may have been to the main office a few times myself as a child, but it is hard to find any kind of logical consequence.

394
00:33:14,823 --> 00:33:19,145
[SPEAKER_10]: And I don't know what the stats are and how often kids are sent to the main office.

395
00:33:20,806 --> 00:33:25,187
[SPEAKER_10]: But recess seems like the worst thing you could do is take recess away.

396
00:33:25,227 --> 00:33:27,088
[SPEAKER_10]: It's like kids need that.

397
00:33:27,688 --> 00:33:33,571
[SPEAKER_10]: And I realize DESE does not count it as educational time, which hopefully I can get some of that fixed.

398
00:33:33,671 --> 00:33:34,992
[SPEAKER_10]: But thank you.

399
00:33:38,213 --> 00:33:39,754
[SPEAKER_06]: Are there any other questions?

