414
00:34:47,562 --> 00:34:52,325
[SPEAKER_18]: So I would say in full transparency, I have not undertaken that work yet.

415
00:34:52,866 --> 00:34:54,087
[SPEAKER_18]: I think it is important work.

416
00:34:54,527 --> 00:35:02,032
[SPEAKER_18]: I would say that at the elementary level, which is to what member Russo had mentioned, we did do that work to align.

417
00:35:02,613 --> 00:35:12,620
[SPEAKER_18]: The way the handbooks have been here historically, and like I said, haven't done a review or an audit, but the school specific information should be at the front.

418
00:35:14,241 --> 00:35:16,763
[SPEAKER_18]: Medford and Commonwealth policies

419
00:35:17,927 --> 00:35:18,727
[SPEAKER_18]: should be at the back.

420
00:35:19,287 --> 00:35:41,113
[SPEAKER_18]: There was some work done at the elementary level pre-COVID though to align so that there was that alignment and it was for, I wouldn't say the sole purpose, but two main reasons was to have some, to make sure that there was alignment amongst the four elementary schools and for translation purposes.

421
00:35:41,673 --> 00:35:45,814
[SPEAKER_18]: So that way, when we're sending out our handbooks to be translated,

422
00:35:46,537 --> 00:35:50,219
[SPEAKER_18]: The policies that were at the back are right.

423
00:35:50,679 --> 00:35:53,741
[SPEAKER_18]: They're all the same and we only have to have that translation done once.

424
00:35:54,421 --> 00:35:58,223
[SPEAKER_18]: And then the school specific translations can be done on an individual basis.

425
00:35:59,063 --> 00:36:03,426
[SPEAKER_18]: But I have there has not been that work at the secondary level at all.

426
00:36:03,506 --> 00:36:15,892
[SPEAKER_18]: So I will I mean I'm happy to review especially the two middle schools for better alignment in terms of layout and format.

427
00:36:17,081 --> 00:36:18,121
[SPEAKER_09]: That's really helpful, thank you.

428
00:36:18,222 --> 00:36:23,704
