00:39:17,333 --> 00:39:20,196
[SPEAKER_10]: It's like we're trying to make it clear that we mean it.

460
00:39:21,978 --> 00:39:26,283
[SPEAKER_10]: But a signature for something that's 70-something pages long that very few people have read

461
00:39:28,095 --> 00:39:31,959
[SPEAKER_10]: It just doesn't feel right.

462
00:39:31,979 --> 00:39:36,483
[SPEAKER_10]: I don't think the signature thing is any kind of mandatory thing.

463
00:39:36,503 --> 00:39:38,825
[SPEAKER_10]: I think that's just something we do, or is it mandatory?

464
00:39:40,787 --> 00:39:41,487
[SPEAKER_10]: I don't know.

465
00:39:41,627 --> 00:39:45,691
[SPEAKER_10]: I'll look into that, but we should revisit the signature thing.

466
00:39:46,472 --> 00:39:52,177
[SPEAKER_10]: Signing that you've received it is one thing, but I believe it does say you have read it and understand it.

467
00:39:54,910 --> 00:39:55,310
[SPEAKER_18]: It does.

468
00:39:55,330 --> 00:40:02,977
[SPEAKER_18]: I hear you, but I also can understand the acknowledgement part of just having some understanding as to what is in there.

469
00:40:03,437 --> 00:40:06,179
[SPEAKER_18]: There's school specific information that's important.

470
00:40:07,260 --> 00:40:20,631
[SPEAKER_18]: I think there are, to your point, I think there are pieces that could definitely be called out, but things around attendance, arrival dismissal, certain procedures like the bullying policy and now the AI, I do think there are some

471
00:40:21,768 --> 00:40:28,391
[SPEAKER_18]: really key pieces of how the schools function that caregivers should be aware of.

472
00:40:28,832 --> 00:40:41,618
[SPEAKER_18]: So there is a balance between reading 70 pages and acknowledging that you have at least skimmed the table of contents.

473
00:40:42,198 --> 00:40:50,883
[SPEAKER_10]: Yeah, at a high level, this is the most important stuff you really need to know, that everybody needs to know, to be a member of the school community.

474
00:40:51,415 --> 00:40:57,217
[SPEAKER_10]: versus a lot of the policies that like, you know, if you're never involved in any bullying incident, you don't have to read that stuff.

475
00:40:57,257 --> 00:41:01,798
[SPEAKER_10]: Like, there's all kinds of things for which you are in there that you may never need to know.

476
00:41:02,518 --> 00:41:08,760
[SPEAKER_10]: And so, I think it would be fine to ask them to sign off on a few pages, five pages, even maybe 10 pages that you've read that.

477
00:41:10,081 --> 00:41:15,942
[SPEAKER_10]: But it's starting to feel like our, you know, every time we upgrade our iPhone software, we, yes, I agree to the 780 pages that nobody other

