[SPEAKER_06]: Hold on one second.

515
00:43:03,732 --> 00:43:04,273
[SPEAKER_02]: There we go.

516
00:43:04,673 --> 00:43:05,053
[SPEAKER_02]: Thank you.

517
00:43:05,574 --> 00:43:06,134
[SPEAKER_02]: Good evening.

518
00:43:06,595 --> 00:43:13,701
[SPEAKER_02]: Tonight I am presenting two updates to current Medford Public Schools policies that require this body's approval.

519
00:43:14,242 --> 00:43:17,565
[SPEAKER_02]: So the first one is the bullying prevention and intervention plan.

520
00:43:18,426 --> 00:43:27,414
[SPEAKER_02]: Currently the district is in the process of completing their self-assessment for the integrated monitoring review and they look at civil rights criteria.

521
00:43:28,235 --> 00:43:41,425
[SPEAKER_02]: And in my review of that criteria, there is some language that is missing that DESE is looking for in order for us to get a proficient rating and that we're meeting this requirement.

522
00:43:42,186 --> 00:43:49,612
[SPEAKER_02]: So the first thing that I wanted to update was the label which says categories of vulnerable students.

523
00:43:50,452 --> 00:43:59,358
[SPEAKER_02]: The paragraph listed under there where it says, as required by Mass General Law, this is already found in the Behavior Intervention Plan on page four.

524
00:44:00,599 --> 00:44:15,249
[SPEAKER_02]: But what I would like to do is have that added again to page eight under the decisions and findings, but also to add this specific language that says, this plan shall afford all students the same protection regardless of their status under the law.

525
00:44:16,009 --> 00:44:35,939
[SPEAKER_02]: as required by Mass General Law, the IEP team or 504 accommodation team must consider what should be included in the plan to develop the student's skills and proficiencies to avoid and respond to bullying, harassment, or teasing if the student's disability affects social skills or makes the student vulnerable.

526
00:44:36,259 --> 00:44:43,843
[SPEAKER_02]: So I'd like to add that language to page eight, and that basically will bring us into compliance with what DESE is requiring for the

527
00:44:44,363 --> 00:44:46,373
[SPEAKER_02]: bullying prevention and intervention plan.

528
00:44:47,857 --> 00:44:55,979
[SPEAKER_02]: And then the next part, which I apologize, it's very lengthy, which I provided to you, but this is the new updated restraint law.

529
00:44:56,939 --> 00:44:59,159
[SPEAKER_02]: There are revised restraint requirements.

530
00:44:59,539 --> 00:45:17,503
[SPEAKER_02]: This update, which I've included in your packet, was drafted in reviewing the new regulations from DESE, but also we had our special education legal counsel provide us with some documents and some language to use when rolling this out

531
00:45:18,243 --> 00:45:21,885
[SPEAKER_02]: and this is coming out, it's effective August 17th of this year.

532
00:45:22,765 --> 00:45:30,348
[SPEAKER_02]: So the first thing is, I do apologize, the policy is lengthy because many of the required procedures are included or referenced.

533
00:45:31,249 --> 00:45:38,612
[SPEAKER_02]: These are not required to be part of the policy but provide a structure and process for school staff and administration to follow.

534
00:45:40,143 --> 00:45:45,089
[SPEAKER_02]: Much of the language around definitions, the use and reporting of restraint is the same.

535
00:45:45,810 --> 00:45:59,625
[SPEAKER_02]: The changes focus on distinguishing seclusion from timeout, the prerequisites required to use emergency seclusion or prone restraint, and the new requirements for any physical space used for timeout.

536
00:46:00,341 --> 00:46:03,362
[SPEAKER_02]: and the requirement to have a grievance procedure.

537
00:46:03,823 --> 00:46:17,009
[SPEAKER_02]: So the chart that I provided that says new restraint law requirements, I basically laid out what the previous practice was and what the current practice, or what the practice will be starting in August 17th of 2026.

538
00:46:17,589 --> 00:46:20,371
[SPEAKER_02]: Definitions that weren't clear are very clear in this document.

539
00:46:30,733 --> 00:46:43,080
[SPEAKER_02]: We have been working with our staff at the Missituck School, our therapeutic learning program, about the rollout of this, what it's going to look like, as well as the documents that go along with this.

540
00:46:43,540 --> 00:46:57,268
[SPEAKER_02]: So once this is, we hope to have everything prepared by the end of the school year, so when we start in September, everything will be up and running, staff will be trained, and all the documents will be updated and ready to go.

541
00:47:02,499 --> 00:47:03,079
[SPEAKER_04]: Member Parks.

542
00:47:04,180 --> 00:47:04,560
[SPEAKER_04]: Thank you.

543
00:47:04,940 --> 00:47:17,383
[SPEAKER_04]: I have just two questions about the new policy.

544
00:47:18,764 --> 00:47:23,425
[SPEAKER_04]: One can you clarify and I know this is part of the law.

545
00:47:24,345 --> 00:47:24,565
[SPEAKER_04]: What.

546
00:47:25,286 --> 00:47:26,366
[SPEAKER_04]: How do you get.

547
00:47:27,807 --> 00:47:31,630
[SPEAKER_04]: parental consent for seclusion.

548
00:47:32,511 --> 00:47:37,275
[SPEAKER_04]: If it cannot be included in the IEP and you need

549
00:47:37,937 --> 00:47:40,799
[SPEAKER_04]: parental consent through a signature of a parent.

550
00:47:41,839 --> 00:47:42,720
[SPEAKER_04]: What is that process?

551
00:47:43,020 --> 00:47:45,521
[SPEAKER_02]: So we're in the process of creating those documents.

552
00:47:45,581 --> 00:47:49,164
[SPEAKER_02]: We do have guidance from DESE of what the language should include.

553
00:47:50,144 --> 00:47:55,347
[SPEAKER_02]: If we do not receive parental permission, we cannot use seclusion.

554
00:47:55,667 --> 00:47:59,830
[SPEAKER_02]: And that is not a practice that the district currently uses at this time.

555
00:48:00,727 --> 00:48:03,429
[SPEAKER_02]: Nor, in my opinion, is something that we should do.

556
00:48:03,870 --> 00:48:06,892
[SPEAKER_02]: Seclusion is a student's locked in a room, not allowed to leave.

557
00:48:07,293 --> 00:48:11,256
[SPEAKER_02]: That's not a therapeutic methodology that I would like staff to be using.

558
00:48:11,816 --> 00:48:12,237
[SPEAKER_04]: Perfect.

559
00:48:12,297 --> 00:48:17,261
[SPEAKER_04]: So then, what have you been using currently at the Mississippi?

560
00:48:17,301 --> 00:48:20,904
[SPEAKER_02]: So we currently have a timeout room, and we also have a sensory room.

561
00:48:21,344 --> 00:48:24,627
[SPEAKER_02]: And at this time, sometimes students need a break and are given

562
00:48:25,688 --> 00:48:27,788
[SPEAKER_02]: Adults provide them with that choice.

563
00:48:27,968 --> 00:48:30,169
[SPEAKER_02]: Sometimes students are asking to take a break.

564
00:48:30,689 --> 00:48:35,270
[SPEAKER_02]: They may go into the timeout room, but a lot of students are choosing the sensory room as well.

565
00:48:35,390 --> 00:48:39,931
[SPEAKER_02]: And then once they're regulated, they're ready to go back to class, they return to class.

566
00:48:41,051 --> 00:48:41,531
[SPEAKER_04]: OK, thank you.

567
00:48:41,751 --> 00:48:52,593
[SPEAKER_04]: And then my last question is, in terms of documenting timeout, I know it's not a requirement by the state to notify parents, similar to how it is a requirement for seclusion.

568
00:48:54,153 --> 00:48:57,976
[SPEAKER_04]: I know it also says it's optional but recommended in our policy.

569
00:48:58,456 --> 00:49:05,261
[SPEAKER_04]: Is there a way that we can kind of make that more of a norm or actually required practice?

570
00:49:05,341 --> 00:49:09,124
[SPEAKER_02]: So we do notify parents if that was to happen.

571
00:49:09,244 --> 00:49:11,846
[SPEAKER_02]: But that's also one of the documents that we're looking at.

572
00:49:11,926 --> 00:49:18,551
[SPEAKER_02]: And we are required to document the restraints and upload that to DESE on a yearly basis.

573
00:49:18,711 --> 00:49:20,113
[SPEAKER_02]: And I have to review them all.

574
00:49:20,793 --> 00:49:30,740
[SPEAKER_02]: I have to go through, you know, if we see the same student all the time, like that's a bigger discussion with staff about what we need to do differently for this student.

575
00:49:31,400 --> 00:49:33,822
[SPEAKER_02]: But we will be notifying parents if this happens.

576
00:49:34,162 --> 00:49:34,302
[SPEAKER_04]: Great.

577
00:49:34,362 --> 00:49:34,722
[SPEAKER_04]: Thank you.

