653
00:56:50,870 --> 00:56:53,592
[SPEAKER_18]: So we looked at redundancies in the space summary.

654
00:56:54,012 --> 00:57:03,477
[SPEAKER_18]: We looked for opportunities to repurpose in the space summary and we looked for opportunities where reductions were necessary.

655
00:57:04,097 --> 00:57:08,099
[SPEAKER_18]: We wanted to make sure that our decisions were farthest away from students.

656
00:57:08,860 --> 00:57:18,905
[SPEAKER_18]: And so we took an approach to really looking at reducing office space because we're prioritizing collaboration which means we are prioritizing

657
00:57:19,537 --> 00:57:28,002
[SPEAKER_18]: conference rooms, which would be the vehicle to get work done, not maintaining private office space.

658
00:57:28,803 --> 00:57:34,987
[SPEAKER_18]: We also took an approach to looking at what are the redundancies and what are the places that we could repurpose.

659
00:57:36,288 --> 00:57:40,911
[SPEAKER_18]: We don't know necessarily what education is going to look like 25 years from now.

660
00:57:42,374 --> 00:57:44,515
[SPEAKER_18]: 10 years from now, maybe even 50 years from now.

661
00:57:44,575 --> 00:57:52,379
[SPEAKER_18]: So it's very important to have spaces that are going to be flexible and grow with the changing needs of the community.

662
00:57:52,460 --> 00:57:58,203
[SPEAKER_18]: So looking at spaces in which we could be the most flexible to do that.

663
00:57:58,583 --> 00:58:01,464
[SPEAKER_18]: Just a high level example would be in the space summary.

664
00:58:01,904 --> 00:58:04,946
[SPEAKER_18]: There were two maker spaces in the space summary.

665
00:58:07,327 --> 00:58:21,507
[SPEAKER_18]: We felt that maintaining one for the purpose of what that is intended but retitling it an innovation lab would serve the purpose of maintaining that space for.

666
00:58:22,505 --> 00:58:27,288
[SPEAKER_18]: flexibility so that teachers could rent out that space, students could use that space.

667
00:58:27,748 --> 00:58:30,149
[SPEAKER_18]: It could be used for a lot of project-based learning.

668
00:58:30,230 --> 00:58:34,832
[SPEAKER_18]: It could be used for a lot of even clubs or enrichments or extracurriculars.

669
00:58:35,473 --> 00:58:41,076
