01:06:49,925 --> 01:06:57,487
[SPEAKER_06]: And we did get confirmation today that the answer for any sort of change to that deed restriction would be an Article 97 process, which is not a short process.

729
01:06:58,387 --> 01:07:13,491
[SPEAKER_06]: So the building committee will consider on Wednesday night whether we want to pursue those or adopt some of the revised design options that would keep two of the three options in play.

730
01:07:15,132 --> 01:07:18,173
[SPEAKER_06]: And we'll see where the building committee sort of falls on that.

731
01:07:18,293 --> 01:07:31,960
[SPEAKER_06]: But all of that is happening at the same time as we are talking about how this oversight happened, who is responsible for the oversight, and to make sure that the city of Medford's interests are protected.

732
01:07:32,060 --> 01:07:35,161
[SPEAKER_06]: So all of that is also going on at the same time.

733
01:07:36,422 --> 01:07:38,763
[SPEAKER_06]: And resolution to that is complicated.

734
01:07:39,643 --> 01:07:49,012
[SPEAKER_06]: and ongoing and probably is not likely to be the source of any sort of resolution by Wednesday night because there's lots of there's lots of parties involved in that conversation.

735
01:07:49,092 --> 01:07:53,235
[SPEAKER_06]: So what we are going to try to do on Wednesday night is make sure that

736
01:07:54,376 --> 01:08:17,996
[SPEAKER_06]: The building committee is clear and aware of the deed restriction and my apologies to the building committee that we were not able to meet before this news sort of made its way into the public conversation because it's certainly always the project team's intention that the building committee knows these things first, but also to give the building committee some options for a path forward.

737
01:08:18,897 --> 01:08:21,880
[SPEAKER_06]: And there are a handful of options which include

738
01:08:22,560 --> 01:08:38,463
[SPEAKER_06]: some reorienting of the buildings in the two C options that we've carried forward to completely steer clear of those restrictions and still preserve a no modular posture, which

739
01:08:39,304 --> 01:08:40,885
[SPEAKER_06]: We were worried was not going to be possible.

740
01:08:40,966 --> 01:09:02,181
[SPEAKER_06]: So all of that is coming on Wednesday night with additional costing information and some, you know, some revision to costing based on the space reductions that have been made, based on updated assumptions, based on all of this like new latest information and in a sort of more comprehensive top to bottom fashion.

741
01:09:02,201 --> 01:09:04,843
[SPEAKER_06]: So there's one place and source for that information.

742
01:09:07,652 --> 01:09:15,042
[SPEAKER_06]: I think that is everything in terms of what I wanted to update you all on, but I did want to open up the floor in case people had questions.

743
01:09:17,691 --> 01:09:18,192
[SPEAKER_06]: Member Einfeld?

744
01:09:18,712 --> 01:09:18,972
[SPEAKER_08]: Yes.

745
01:09:20,293 --> 01:09:24,677
[SPEAKER_08]: Did the MSBA request specific changes to the educational plan?

746
01:09:25,098 --> 01:09:29,401
[SPEAKER_08]: I know you said you're in the process of responding and that it will likely come back to us.

747
01:09:30,542 --> 01:09:36,648
[SPEAKER_08]: Is it possible for us to see what those changes were since we did approve this plan as a body?

748
01:09:37,190 --> 01:09:46,953
[SPEAKER_06]: Yeah, I mean, we can certainly share with this body the response that sort of frames, like, the answers to their questions, which I think would give you a better orientation of, like, what's to come in the ed plan.

749
01:09:47,973 --> 01:09:52,034
[SPEAKER_06]: I wouldn't say that anything they did requested a change to the ed plan.

750
01:09:52,054 --> 01:09:55,615
[SPEAKER_06]: That's really not the MSBA's, like, goal in any of this.

751
01:09:56,695 --> 01:10:04,740
[SPEAKER_06]: They asked questions about things that were maybe unclear or newer, like our schedule is evolving, so they had questions about that.

752
01:10:05,800 --> 01:10:13,204
[SPEAKER_06]: I think the project team's opinion so far has been that cleaning that up will change the ed plan in so much as it's clarifying.

753
01:10:14,325 --> 01:10:19,946
[SPEAKER_06]: here's where we were, here's where we are now, here's where we plan to be by the time we have a new high school.

754
01:10:20,006 --> 01:10:26,688
[SPEAKER_06]: So that will change in the ed plan, but it's not, they didn't come back and say, we disagree with your ed plan.

755
01:10:26,728 --> 01:10:29,428
[SPEAKER_06]: That's sort of not the goal of their comments.

756
01:10:29,588 --> 01:10:35,009
[SPEAKER_06]: The goal of their comments is more to match, to make sure that the space matches the ed plan.

757
01:10:35,069 --> 01:10:38,610
[SPEAKER_06]: And the other thing that they had questions about was like Medford Academy.

758
01:10:39,130 --> 01:10:41,831
[SPEAKER_06]: where Medford Academy is a new program.

759
01:10:41,971 --> 01:10:43,912
[SPEAKER_06]: It's new since our statement of interest.

760
01:10:44,032 --> 01:10:45,893
[SPEAKER_06]: It's new since our eligibility documents.

761
01:10:45,973 --> 01:10:49,955
[SPEAKER_06]: And so I think they were seeking clarity around like, does this exist now?

762
01:10:50,235 --> 01:10:54,376
[SPEAKER_06]: Or is it something you hope to do in the future so we can answer that question?

763
01:10:54,476 --> 01:10:56,637
[SPEAKER_06]: And then I think that will satisfy things.

764
01:10:56,757 --> 01:10:57,978
[SPEAKER_06]: Seems totally reasonable.

765
01:10:58,318 --> 01:11:13,224
[SPEAKER_06]: Yeah the comments actually overall like I actually pulled Salem High School's documents to say even for myself like how does what we received compare to what other communities receive at this stage in the game and it was very comparable.

766
01:11:14,024 --> 01:11:14,524
[SPEAKER_06]: That's great.

767
01:11:14,825 --> 01:11:17,666
[SPEAKER_08]: And I'm also actually very glad to hear that we are.

768
01:11:18,147 --> 01:11:24,931
[SPEAKER_08]: I really love that the building committee did this in the last meeting to say what are options A B C D for the auditorium.

769
01:11:24,991 --> 01:11:30,294
[SPEAKER_08]: So I appreciate I know it's really hard to look at things in isolation and to

770
01:11:30,914 --> 01:11:44,762
[SPEAKER_08]: But I think that's really helpful in thinking about well if we don't do this as part of this project what does that mean and how does it affect what some other plan is which I know is also hard to quantify because you're talking about renovating an old building and turning it into.

771
01:11:45,295 --> 01:11:51,556
[SPEAKER_08]: a preschool like the toilets like that retrofitting is not your typical oh yes just bringing it up to code.

772
01:11:51,897 --> 01:11:55,797
[SPEAKER_08]: So I appreciate that any ability we have to make those decisions.

773
01:11:57,078 --> 01:12:05,580
[SPEAKER_08]: I do want to on record just express disappointment that this deed restriction got past that in that feasibility.

774
01:12:06,600 --> 01:12:16,929
[SPEAKER_08]: It's upsetting that this wasn't caught and we're moving on, that's the important part, but I just think it's important to say that it's really unfortunate because I think it caused a lot of consternation.

775
01:12:17,649 --> 01:12:32,442
[SPEAKER_08]: And then my question around that is if the building committee recommends trying to get that lifted, does MSBA, does the process have a pause button that would allow for something like this or no?

776
01:12:33,462 --> 01:12:35,844
[SPEAKER_06]: I think we would have to be in conversation with the MSBA.

777
01:12:35,924 --> 01:12:38,165
[SPEAKER_06]: They are aware of the deed restriction.

778
01:12:38,585 --> 01:12:42,728
[SPEAKER_06]: As soon as we became aware of it, we let them know, which is what we're required to do.

779
01:12:42,748 --> 01:12:47,430
[SPEAKER_06]: I think this stuff is fairly common for them in their world.

780
01:12:49,231 --> 01:12:56,677
[SPEAKER_06]: It feels like a really big surprise for us, and I think it is, but I think big surprises happen on these kinds of projects all the time.

781
01:12:56,717 --> 01:13:01,701
[SPEAKER_06]: So they understood sort of what we were doing and the steps we were taking.

782
01:13:01,841 --> 01:13:11,168
[SPEAKER_06]: If we had to, if we, well, if the building committee wanted to proceed with an option that would require an Article 97, there probably is a timeline.

783
01:13:11,808 --> 01:13:24,686
[SPEAKER_06]: impact to that that we would have to work through with MSBA because the question is really about sequence of events and how done does that process have to be before you can start designing a building, et cetera, et cetera.

784
01:13:24,726 --> 01:13:27,670
[SPEAKER_06]: So I think that would be a pretty collaborative conversation for us to have to have.

785
01:13:28,191 --> 01:13:28,451
[SPEAKER_08]: Okay.

786
01:13:28,551 --> 01:13:35,273
[SPEAKER_08]: And I will say I'm very encouraged that the project team was able to spring into action and create some new designs.

787
01:13:35,373 --> 01:13:36,013
[SPEAKER_08]: Me too.

788
01:13:36,534 --> 01:13:51,798
[SPEAKER_08]: So as disappointed as I am that this happened, I have been impressed with the response of notifying and moving forward and looking at options, not catastrophizing and just really putting heads down and figuring out what solutions were.

789
01:13:51,878 --> 01:13:54,039
[SPEAKER_08]: So I want to thank everyone involved with that.

790
01:13:55,279 --> 01:13:56,880
[SPEAKER_08]: And that's it from me, at least for now.

791
01:14:00,653 --> 01:14:03,556
[SPEAKER_06]: Are there any other questions from the committee?

792
01:14:05,257 --> 01:14:05,938
[SPEAKER_06]: Member Russo?

793
01:14:06,578 --> 01:14:07,018
[SPEAKER_10]: Thank you.

794
01:14:08,820 --> 01:14:16,766
[SPEAKER_10]: You know, one of the things about the Article 97, first of all, they are very common, and they have a very high pass rate.

795
01:14:17,307 --> 01:14:18,628
[SPEAKER_10]: They have to go through the legislature.

796
01:14:20,389 --> 01:14:25,053
[SPEAKER_10]: And one of the things I think we need to get a really solid understanding of is,

797
01:14:26,842 --> 01:14:30,325
[SPEAKER_10]: Is there sort of like an MO, a memorandum of understanding or something that can be done?

798
01:14:30,345 --> 01:14:31,365
[SPEAKER_10]: No.

799
01:14:31,705 --> 01:14:42,093
[SPEAKER_10]: So we would not be able to hire a construction manager to begin the project with the assumption that this will actually be done.

800
01:14:43,832 --> 01:14:48,253
[SPEAKER_06]: I think that's the question we would have to have conversation about.

801
01:14:49,373 --> 01:14:53,494
[SPEAKER_06]: There is no MOA that's going to come forward that says, like, this is going to be fine.

802
01:14:53,974 --> 01:14:57,475
[SPEAKER_06]: Article 97, I think, requires a two-thirds voice vote of the legislature.

803
01:14:57,555 --> 01:15:03,916
[SPEAKER_06]: So I don't think anybody is willing ever to be like, yes, I will get two-thirds of the legislature to agree with this thing.

804
01:15:03,996 --> 01:15:09,017
[SPEAKER_06]: So no, there will not be anything like that coming forward.

805
01:15:09,377 --> 01:15:12,898
[SPEAKER_06]: We were able to confirm that today in our conversation with DCR.

806
01:15:14,976 --> 01:15:26,559
[SPEAKER_06]: However, that doesn't mean that everything has to stop or that our CM couldn't come on board, but it would mean like if we needed to pursue one of those options, we would have to have some conversation with the MSBA.

807
01:15:27,260 --> 01:15:29,580
[SPEAKER_06]: The Article 97 process is not inexpensive.

808
01:15:30,680 --> 01:15:36,042
[SPEAKER_06]: It generally does take quite a long time, like moving really lightning fast is like four to six months.

809
01:15:37,563 --> 01:15:42,769
[SPEAKER_06]: And then we you know we will bump into the legislative recess and all of those good things.

810
01:15:42,809 --> 01:15:48,435
[SPEAKER_06]: So it'll be interesting to see what the building committee decides to do on Wednesday night.

811
01:15:48,576 --> 01:15:55,704
[SPEAKER_06]: But there is a motion that was at least drafted so that the public could read it and digest it.

812
01:15:55,764 --> 01:15:56,184
[SPEAKER_06]: That would.

813
01:15:57,105 --> 01:16:11,221
[SPEAKER_06]: to actually formally take three options off the table and insert two options for consideration of these revised alternatives so that if the committee chooses to take that up there's some like notice in preparation for the community to participate in that.

814
01:16:12,162 --> 01:16:12,562
[SPEAKER_10]: Thank you.

815
01:16:16,347 --> 01:16:17,228
[SPEAKER_06]: Any other questions?

816
01:16:18,935 --> 01:16:20,695
[SPEAKER_08]: This might be a question for Wednesday.

817
01:16:20,935 --> 01:16:27,117
[SPEAKER_08]: If the committee votes to put those two options, how does that affect the cost analysis that's happening now?

818
01:16:27,897 --> 01:16:37,798
[SPEAKER_06]: We confirmed today that the costing is equivalent because they are substantially the same designs as the 2C options were before.

819
01:16:38,879 --> 01:16:45,000
[SPEAKER_06]: And so there's not a cost estimating concern.

820
01:16:45,380 --> 01:16:45,660
[SPEAKER_06]: OK.

821
01:16:45,920 --> 01:16:46,180
[SPEAKER_08]: Thank you.

822
01:16:49,272 --> 01:16:53,543
[SPEAKER_06]: Any other questions from the committee?

823
01:16:54,065 --> 01:16:54,727
[SPEAKER_06]: Member Master Boeing.

824
01:16:58,872 --> 01:17:04,035
[SPEAKER_09]: Briefly, who's managing the Article 97 process from Medford residents' perspective?

825
01:17:04,096 --> 01:17:05,616
[SPEAKER_09]: Is that, who's responsible for that?

826
01:17:05,676 --> 01:17:09,699
[SPEAKER_09]: It's the, you know, our consultants, the school building committee, the mayor's office.

827
01:17:09,719 --> 01:17:11,260
[SPEAKER_09]: Like, you know, who's coordinating that?

828
01:17:11,300 --> 01:17:17,984
[SPEAKER_09]: I understand, you know, we all want to be speaking with the same voice, marching in the same direction to get the legislature to get where we need them to.

829
01:17:18,865 --> 01:17:21,106
[SPEAKER_09]: I guess that's my question.

830
01:17:21,126 --> 01:17:22,247
[SPEAKER_09]: Who's leading the charge here?

831
01:17:23,725 --> 01:17:29,347
[SPEAKER_06]: That's actually a great question and the answer to that is not entirely like perfectly clear yet.

832
01:17:29,407 --> 01:17:39,051
[SPEAKER_06]: So Article 97 the first thing that has to happen is you engage a land use attorney and they really help guide and shepherd the project through that process.

833
01:17:39,651 --> 01:17:42,833
[SPEAKER_06]: And we're in the process of talking to several land use attorneys to

834
01:17:43,773 --> 01:17:46,855
[SPEAKER_06]: formally bring somebody into that if we choose to go that route.

835
01:17:48,196 --> 01:17:52,959
[SPEAKER_06]: But Article 97 does require things like land swaps, etc.

836
01:17:52,979 --> 01:17:58,343
[SPEAKER_06]: So the city of Medford will have to be involved in that because this school committee nor the building committee own land.

837
01:17:58,563 --> 01:18:05,148
[SPEAKER_06]: Those those parcel any parcel that might be involved would have to come from like a recommendation from the city.

838
01:18:05,228 --> 01:18:05,368
[SPEAKER_06]: So

839
01:18:05,748 --> 01:18:09,711
[SPEAKER_06]: That's why the land use attorney is so important, because there are a lot of tentacles.

840
01:18:09,811 --> 01:18:15,835
[SPEAKER_06]: And the project team will have to be called on to do some things in terms of environmental impact.

841
01:18:17,176 --> 01:18:20,719
[SPEAKER_06]: And then the city will be called upon to do things, and the building committee.

842
01:18:20,739 --> 01:18:25,142
[SPEAKER_06]: So the land use attorney would really shepherd us through that process.

843
01:18:26,763 --> 01:18:28,504
[SPEAKER_06]: And it would take all of us.

844
01:18:28,624 --> 01:18:30,305
[SPEAKER_06]: But the process itself is...

845
01:18:32,368 --> 01:18:38,295
[SPEAKER_06]: You know, it costs money on its own to even make the process happen because of all the moving parts.

846
01:18:41,780 --> 01:18:44,263
[SPEAKER_09]: And the SBC chooses the attorney?

847
01:18:46,283 --> 01:18:48,044
[SPEAKER_06]: That's a great question.

848
01:18:49,925 --> 01:18:55,788
[SPEAKER_06]: We would have to determine who the land use attorney works for and on behalf of.

849
01:18:56,428 --> 01:19:01,431
[SPEAKER_06]: And if it's the city of Medford, I think I would need guidance to answer that question correctly.

850
01:19:02,551 --> 01:19:03,712
[SPEAKER_06]: Not 100% clear.

851
01:19:04,552 --> 01:19:05,793
[SPEAKER_09]: Curious, but I'm sure we'll figure it out.

852
01:19:05,973 --> 01:19:06,153
[SPEAKER_09]: Yeah.

853
01:19:06,373 --> 01:19:07,394
[SPEAKER_09]: Let me know if you need help.

854
01:19:09,875 --> 01:19:14,237
[SPEAKER_03]: If I could, Member Graham, to just say that a lot of the internal

855
01:19:14,835 --> 01:19:19,097
[SPEAKER_03]: meetings that we've been having, especially as of late with all the issues we're dealing with.

856
01:19:20,058 --> 01:19:34,705
[SPEAKER_03]: Member Graham, Dr. Galluzzi, and myself have been the ones meeting with the delegation, discussing the land use attorneys, and really collaborating to try to get through this difficult-ish time.

857
01:19:35,426 --> 01:19:43,970
[SPEAKER_03]: And then I just also want to add that the PDT feedback and the responses that our consultants are working on

858
01:19:44,615 --> 01:19:49,057
[SPEAKER_03]: are being provided to the MSBC committee on Wednesday.

859
01:19:49,077 --> 01:20:02,323
[SPEAKER_03]: So I just ask that that be forwarded to the school committee so you also can read the full PDP responses from the MSBA, if you'd like, or throw it into AI and get a summary generated for you.

860
01:20:02,343 --> 01:20:06,925
[SPEAKER_03]: Let's see the city's responses along with the school building committee.

861
01:20:09,086 --> 01:20:10,027
[SPEAKER_06]: Yep, we can send that along.

862
01:20:13,636 --> 01:20:14,116
[SPEAKER_04]: Member Parks.

863
01:20:15,277 --> 01:20:17,219
[SPEAKER_04]: That actually was a little bit of my question.

864
01:20:17,439 --> 01:20:25,424
[SPEAKER_04]: Would we be able to see those questions and responses and you had mentioned Salem and looking at those.

865
01:20:26,445 --> 01:20:32,509
[SPEAKER_04]: Is the project team also said that these are you know in line with comments that they receive.

866
01:20:33,212 --> 01:20:47,552
[SPEAKER_04]: in terms of just asking for these clarifications and kind of basically dotting your I's, crossing your T's, and really reinforcing what is said in kind of a, yes, this is what we mean kind of manner, if that's what I heard correctly, as you were saying.

867
01:20:49,243 --> 01:20:49,944
[SPEAKER_06]: Yes, they have.

868
01:20:50,004 --> 01:20:57,089
[SPEAKER_06]: I don't know if maybe that's better suited for Wednesday's meeting, but they're on the call, so I'm sure they'd be happy to answer that.

869
01:20:57,769 --> 01:21:03,393
[SPEAKER_06]: I don't know, Jen or Matt Rice, if you would like to take a answer at that question.

870
01:21:04,513 --> 01:21:05,074
[SPEAKER_05]: Absolutely.

871
01:21:05,094 --> 01:21:06,975
[SPEAKER_05]: This is Jen Carlson with left field.

872
01:21:07,655 --> 01:21:11,598
[SPEAKER_05]: I'll start and then Matt, if you want to add any color.

873
01:21:12,440 --> 01:21:19,164
[SPEAKER_05]: Yes, I would say these comments are typical for the PDP feedback that we receive from the MSBA.

874
01:21:19,984 --> 01:21:32,531
[SPEAKER_05]: At this stage, we typically see them looking to clarify the ed plan since submitting with the PDP package is the first time that they're seeing the ed plan and reviewing it.

875
01:21:33,551 --> 01:21:35,792
[SPEAKER_05]: to start asking some of their questions.

876
01:21:36,532 --> 01:21:47,957
[SPEAKER_05]: All of the questions that we've seen in there are really in line with what we see across projects, looking for clarification on schedule and new programs, just as Dr. Galluzzi had outlined.

877
01:21:47,977 --> 01:21:49,597
[SPEAKER_05]: Matt Rice.

878
01:21:52,491 --> 01:21:56,917
[SPEAKER_16]: Yeah, I can also just add that we did share, I'm sorry, Matt Rice with SMMA.

879
01:21:58,078 --> 01:22:10,755
